</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1004,2003]" pageId="21" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1940,1966]" pageId="21" pageNumber="60">Comments:</emphasis>
This Central American species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[839,949,1940,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Micropezidae" genus="Paragrallomyia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thiemei">
<emphasis box="[839,949,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="60">P. thiemei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, differing mainly by the conspicuously developed and curved male genital fork arms and the brownish colour of the head.
</paragraph>
